title: Bug 121170 - get column label from meta data object should return some user recognizable strings
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, it returns an empty string instead of a user recognizable label for the column.
EB: The IMetaData.getColumnLabel() method should return a user recognizable label for the column.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before extracting data from the column.
2. Note the returned value, which is an empty string.
